If tag is empty, the 50 most popular hashtags will be returned. operationId: Marks#hashtags parameters: - description: Hashtag to search for in: query name: tag required: false schema: type: string responses: "200": description: No response was specified "400": description: Bad Request summary: Fetches popular hashtags or marks tagged with specified hashtag tags: - marks /api/marks: get: description: >- The main method for querying the marks database. You may use the following options:
  1. No parameters to retrieve all marks in descending chronological order (use before for pagination)
  2. popular (and optionally last_popular_id) to retrieve all popular marks
  3. featured to retrieve all featured marks
  4. x & y to retrieve mark at specific coordinate
  5. user to retrieve all marks created by the specified user
  6. collection to retrieve all marks collected by the specified user
